# Web UI Projects: Interactive Navbar & Stopwatch Application

This repository contains two mini web projects built using **HTML**, **CSS**, and **JavaScript**:

1. ✅ **Task 1**: Interactive Fixed Navigation Menu  
2. ⏱ **Task 2**: Stopwatch Web Application

These projects are designed for learning and practice in building interactive, responsive, and functional user interfaces using web technologies.

---

## 📌 Task 1: Interactive Navigation Menu

### 🔍 Description

An interactive and fixed-position navigation menu that:

- Changes background or style when the user **scrolls** the page
- Applies color and transformation effects when **hovering** over menu items
- Highlights the **active section** based on scroll position
- Works responsively with a **mobile toggle menu**

### 🚀 Features

- Fixed on top and visible on all pages
- Dynamic scroll and hover effects
- Smooth scrolling to sections
- Scroll progress indicator
- Active link highlighting
- Responsive design with mobile support

### 📸 Preview

> ![Navbar Preview](demo-navbar.gif) *(Replace with actual image or GIF)*

---

## ⏱ Task 2: Stopwatch Web Application

### 🔍 Description

A user-friendly stopwatch web app that allows users to:

- **Start**, **pause**, and **reset** the timer
- **Record lap times**
- See time updates in **real-time** using `setInterval()`

### 🚀 Features

- Displays hours, minutes, seconds, and milliseconds
- Start/Pause toggle
- Reset button to clear timer and laps
- Lap time recorder with lap count
- Responsive, minimal design

### 📸 Preview

> ![Stopwatch Preview](demo-stopwatch.gif) *(Replace with actual image or GIF)*

---

## 🛠 Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3 (Flexbox, Transitions, Media Queries)
- JavaScript (DOM Manipulation, Timing Functions, Events)

